SIMPLE: muddy
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muddy
<hw>Mud"dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Muddier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Muddiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding in mud;
besmeared or dashed with mud; <as>as, a <ex>muddy</ex> road or path;
<ex>muddy</ex> boots.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Turbid with mud; <as>as, <ex>muddy</ex>
water</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Consisting of mud or earth; gross; impure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>muddy</qex> vesture of decay.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Confused, as if turbid with mud; cloudy in mind;
dull; stupid; also, immethodical; incoherent; vague.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cold hearts and <qex>muddy</qex> understandings.</q>
<rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Dost think I am so <qex>muddy</qex>, so unsettled.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Not clear or bright.</def>
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muddy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Muddy
<hw>Mud"dy</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Muddied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Muddying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To soil
with mud; to dirty; to render turbid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>(Fig.)</mark>: <def>To cloud; to make dull or
heavy; to confuse.</def> <rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muddy-headed</ent>⟦br⟧
